data.content:
Here are the idiomatic MSTest replacements:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetActiveUsers_ReturnsOnlyActiveUsers()
{
    var service = new UserService();
    var users = service.GetActiveUsers();

    // Count > 0 → specific count or IsNotNull + AreEqual
    Assert.AreEqual(3, users.Count);

    // All match predicate → loop for clear failure messages
    foreach (var user in users)
    {
        Assert.IsTrue(user.IsActive, $"User {user.Name} is not active");
    }

    // != null → IsNotNull
    var admin = users.SingleOrDefault(u => u.Role == "Admin");
    Assert.IsNotNull(admin);
}
```

**Key replacements:**

| Instead of | Use |
|---|---|
| `Assert.IsTrue(x == 3)` | `Assert.AreEqual(3, x)` |
| `Assert.IsTrue(x != null)` | `Assert.IsNotNull(x)` |
| `Assert.IsTrue(x > 0)` | `Assert.AreNotEqual(0, x)` |
| `Assert.IsTrue(list.Contains(x))` | `CollectionAssert.Contains(list, x)` |

The benefit: when tests fail, you get diagnostic messages like `"Expected: 3, Actual: 1"` instead of just `"Assert.IsTrue failed"`.
